3.3	System Requirements

3.3.1	Functional Requirements
•	The system shall allow users to register, log in, and manage their profiles securely.
•	The system shall support CRUD operations for all major entities.
•	The system shall expose RESTful APIs for frontend-backend communication.
•	The system shall implement JWT-based authentication for secure user sessions.
 
•	The system shall generate test reports and maintain a defect log using JIRA.
•	The system shall support role-based access control (Admin, User).
The user registration module required the system to validate email formats, enforce strong password policies (minimum 8 characters with at least one uppercase letter, one number, and one special character), and send a verification email upon successful registration. The profile management module allowed users to update their personal information, upload profile pictures, and change passwords with appropriate validation.
The CRUD operations were defined for multiple entities including user profiles, product listings, and order records. Each operation was governed by role-based access control, ensuring that only authorized users could create, update, or delete records. Administrators were granted full access while regular users were restricted to read and limited update operations on their own records.
