•	Performance: Application should respond to user requests within 2 seconds under normal load conditions.
•	Scalability: Architecture should support horizontal scaling for increased user loads.
•	Security: All data transfers must be encrypted; sensitive data must be hashed.
•	Scalability: Architecture should support horizontal scaling for increased user loads.
 
The non-functional requirements played a critical role in shaping the architecture and technology choices for the project. The performance requirement of sub-2-second response times under normal load was validated through load testing using Apache JMeter, with simulated concurrent users sending requests to Security was addressed at multiple layers of the application.
Transport layer security was enforced by configuring HTTPS with SSL certificates. Application layer security was implemented using Helmet.js to set secure HTTP headers, rate limiting to prevent brute-force attacks, and input sanitization to guard against SQL injection and cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. Sensitive user data such as passwords were hashed using bcrypt with a salt factor of 12, ensuring that even in the event of a data breach, passwords remain unreadable.
